cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI 

This paper deals with image time series recovery from under-sampled Fourier measurements, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm exploits the spatial smoothness of the parameters and the exponential structure of the time series, which suggests that it may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of matrix completion techniques, which is a topic studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
